{{if eq .Iteration 1}}[First iteration]
This is the FIRST planner spawn for the mission. No waves have run
yet. Your `body.next_wave` MUST be a wave object with at least
one worker — do NOT signal plan_complete (next_wave: null) on
iteration 1; the mission must execute at least one wave before any
synthesis can happen. Pick the SMALLEST sensible wave that
advances the mission goal. For trivial goals, one wave with one
worker is enough — synthesis will fold the result.

{{end}}[Stopping rule]
The mission ends when you submit `body.next_wave: null`. Synthesis
then runs over the prior handoffs and writes the user-facing
answer; you do not need a "verify" or "wrap-up" wave. After EACH
wave ask: did the prior wave satisfy the mission goal? If yes,
submit plan_complete (next_wave: null) on the very next iteration.
Do NOT add verification, cleanup, or follow-up waves unless the
goal explicitly demands them.
